<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3342274446" country="Iran" location="Kerman" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kerman">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry box="[353,409,1297,1320]" name="Iran" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation box="[426,510,1296,1321]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–25. 20" captionStartId="75.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-70@75.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 20–25. 20. Trapelus agilis. Blue square denotes the type locality for T. a. khuzistanensis, dashed line delimits approximate boundary between this and the nominotypical subspecies. 21. Trapelus persicus. 22. Trapelus ruderatus. 23. Trapelus sanguinolentus. 24. Anguis colchica. 25. Pseudopus apodus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929715/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
. Most of the western provinces in the Mesopotamian Plain and along the Zagros range up to western 
<collectingRegion box="[378,468,1333,1356]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Kerman</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[523,722,1333,1357]" country="Iran" name="Hormozgan" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Hormozgan Prov.</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1152,1573]" box="[151,1317,1368,1393]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
HABITAT. Sandy areas, on sand dune foothills and near shrubs where they seek refuge (
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S. C." box="[1127,1305,1368,1393]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref45318" refString="Anderson, S. C. (1999) The lizards of Iran. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford, Ohio, 442 pp." type="book" year="1999">Anderson 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1152,1573]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
REMARKS. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rastegar-Pouyani, N." box="[277,558,1404,1429]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="91 - 102" refId="ref62704" refString="Rastegar-Pouyani, N. (2000) Taxonomic status of Trapelus ruderatus (Olivier) and T. persicus (Blanford), and validity of T. lessonae (de Filippi). Amphibia-Reptilia, 21, 91 - 102. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1163 / 156853800507309" type="journal article" year="2000">Rastegar-Pouyani (2000)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blanford" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[721,843,1405,1428]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Trapelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[721,843,1405,1428]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">T. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[907,1046,1404,1429]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Trapelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruderatus">
<emphasis box="[907,1046,1404,1429]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">T. ruderatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however this change was rejected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ananjeva, N. B. &amp; David, P. &amp; Barabanov, A. V. &amp; Dubois, A." box="[188,450,1440,1465]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="197 - 202" refId="ref44905" refString="Ananjeva, N. B., David, P., Barabanov, A. V. &amp; Dubois, A. (2013) On the type specimens of Trapelus ruderatus (Olivier, 1804) and some nomenclatural problems on Trapelus Cuvier, 1816 (Agamidae, Sauria). Russian Journal of Herpetology, 20, 197 - 202." type="journal article" year="2013">
Ananjeva 
<emphasis box="[305,364,1440,1465]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
. The distribution of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blanford" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[688,813,1441,1464]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Trapelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[688,813,1441,1464]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">T. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
overlaps partially with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[1089,1230,1440,1465]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Trapelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruderatus">
<emphasis box="[1089,1230,1440,1465]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">T. ruderatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[1271,1367,1440,1465]" country="Iran" name="Bushehr" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Bushehr</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1381,1432,1441,1464]" country="Iran" name="Fars" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fars</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,244,1476,1501]" country="Iran" name="Esfahan" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Esfahan</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[302,421,1476,1501]" country="Iran" name="Ilam" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Ilam Prov.</collectingRegion>
(Fathinia &amp; Rastegar-Pouyani 2011).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
